<h2 id="mundane-to-memorable">Mundane to Memorable</h2>

<p>As I went along with this exercise, I started to notice that I was lacking substance with the more habitual events of my life.</p>

<p>If I had a funny conversation with a co-worker or a meal that day was phenomenal, anything that broke the norm for the day, I would write it down in an effort to turn that seemingly very average day into something a little more memorable.</p>

<p>When you have a set schedule, whether it be work or school or other commitments youâ€™ve made, a lot of the days can start to just blend together. Days get repetitive, itâ€™s hard to differentiate what you did at work from one day to the next. Seeing a blank or regularly scheduled slate deterred me a bit, it felt I was just going through the motions.</p>

<p>An additional goal of mine was to make the days that blended together a little more distinguishable by adding smaller events that stook out to me. If I had a funny conversation with a co-worker or a meal that day was phenomenal, anything that broke the norm for the day, I would write it down in an effort to turn that seemingly very average day into something a little more memorable.</p>

